    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-12-09T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-12-09T13:00:00-05:00" n="260"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d260">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/29370: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract—Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-09T12:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 9, 1928—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received December 10—1:08 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>319.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>The Minister of Finance, Montes de Oca, has requested that Mr. Morrow be informed
                    that political events of the past week have rendered it desirable to leave debt
                    negotiations and plans for railroad reorganization <hi rend="italic">in statu
                        quo</hi> until the situation becomes somewhat clarified, which might be
                    within a few days or a few weeks. The Minister of Finance does not know, as yet,
                    just what effect General Calles’ change in political plans may have on his
                    position in regard to railroad reorganization.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
